item.title: ioCan You Believe How Many People Don't Know How to Spell 'Ohio'? Find Out Now!
item.description: IV. Conclusion Introduction to Ohio Ohio is a state in the Midwestern United States. It is the 34th largest state in terms of population, with an estimated 11. million people living there. Ohio is known for its diverse landscape, including the Appalachian Mountains, Lake Erie, and the Ohio River. However, one thing that many people don’t know about Ohio is how to spell it. Common Mistakes Many people make the mistake of spelling Ohio as “Oio” or “Oho.
